comment.narrative:
Target 1
1.1 2 Doppler water meters and 9 automated meteo stations installed and they are adequate coverage and greater scope of required data;
1.2 At least 5,000 km2 of the Karakalpakstan region covered by automated hydro-meteorological observation network;
1.3 6 months lead time drought early warning developed and are available for end-users
1.4.1 3 Extension Services established and delivered trainings for subsistence dekhan farmers with provision of knowledge products;
1.4.2 At least 5% (at least 20% of them are female) of Dekhkan farmers and pastoralists of Karakalpakstan region served by science-based extension.

Target 2
2.1 At least 5,000 (25% of women) Dekhkan farmers adopted climate resilient conservation agriculture practices (low till, mixed cropping, fodder production, and residue crop soil);
2.2 At least 5,000 (25% of women)Dekhan farmers adopted water saving irrigation practices (e.g. land levelling, furrow, drip irrigation systems) at 1,000 ha dekhkan farms to improve farm-level drainage and minimise salinization);
2.3 5% (800 of households (2 women-led) or approx. 4,000 people) of targeted Dekhan farmers have established horticulture greenhouses on 2,000 ha of farms to minimise impacts of droughts on farm production;
2.4 One (1) law/regulation on agricultural practices and water management amended and integrated regulations on the adoption of conservation agriculture and water saving techniques and technologies on the farms.

Target 3
3.1 Over 15,000 ha of arid land of Karakalpakstan covered with saksaul and tamarix plantations to deliver sand stabilization and soil desalinization function;
3.2 43,000 people (50% of women) organized in 10 cooperatives based on khokimiyat and makhalla and participate in sand stabilization plantation scheme;
3.3 At least 10 community organizations (at least 5 female groups and village organizations) at khokimiyat and makhalla level have clear mandates, institutional capacities and skills and manage saksaul and tamarix plantations.

Target 4
4.1 A bulletin included information about results of inventory of all tested agronomic measures and successful practices mapped out;
4.2 At least 5 lessons learned for climate resilient agricultural and pastoral production systems in arid lands developed and included into associated publications and web-based disseminated;
4.3 At least 2 farm and pasture land demonstration meetings with participation of national, local authorities, media and communities, and associated printing and publications produced and disseminated.

Target 5
